It’s been a rough few days 😢 Z started having seizures again this week. This is video of him finally coming to after one. The seizures never last long, but the postictal state is lasting hours. He acts blind, completely disoriented and anxious. I started him on meds Thursday night so praying they start working soon!

I knew when I signed up to be a handler, I was signing up for heartbreak, but I never dreamed it would come this soon. K9 Zorro passed away today at home. His stomach flipped today while I was at work and I came home to find him deceased. My heart is beyond broken, I keep asking myself if there was anything I could have done, but he showed absolutely no symptoms at all when I left for work this morning.

I’m so thankful he got to finish his career with me and I know he had an incredible life and was loved by so many. Devastated doesn’t begin to describe how I’m feeling though. No amount of time with him would have been enough, but I definitely thought I had a few more years with him. 

Thank you to everyone who has cheered me and Zorro on for the last 8 years. He was the greatest partner a girl could possibly dream of and I am already lost without him.

Butler Township Police K9 Celebration
Wednesday, August 16th from 6:00-8:00pm
Butler Township Hall, 3780 Little York Road

Join us to celebrate K9 Mando joining our department and to remember K9 Zorro!

K9 Mando began with Officer Streck in April 2023, completed Ohio Certification on June 30 and began working the road on July 2.

K9 Zorro began with Sergeant Carr in April 2015, he retired in December 2022 after serving our community for 7.5 years. K9 Zorro passed away unexpectedly on May 16.

Sergeant Carr, Officer Streck and K9 Mando will be at the event for a meet and greet

Everyone meet Brownie! Found him at the Miami County Animal Shelter, his eyes immediately reminded me of Z. He is one of 32 dogs taken from a hoarding house in Troy.
 
He is supposedly boxer/lab mix, but he is just the best boy! He had no idea how to play, so we’re working on that. But he will not leave my side, which I love because he reminds me of Z!
